  "body_sections": [
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Container for the slow Mersenne Twister pseudo-random number generator. Consider using a different BitGenerator with the Generator container instead."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "RandomState"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Generator"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " expose a number of methods for generating\nrandom numbers drawn from a variety of probability distributions. In\naddition to the distribution-specific arguments, each method takes a\nkeyword argument "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/size/",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "size",
              "text": "size"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " that defaults to "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "None"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". If "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/size/",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "size",
              "text": "size"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "None"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ",\nthen a single value is generated and returned. If "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/size/",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "size",
              "text": "size"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is an integer,\nthen a 1-D array filled with generated values is returned. If "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/size/",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "size",
              "text": "size"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a\ntuple, then an array with that shape is filled and returned."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "strong",
              "text": "Compatibility Guarantee"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "A fixed bit generator using a fixed seed and a fixed series of calls to\n'RandomState' methods using the same parameters will always produce the\nsame results up to roundoff error except when the values were incorrect.\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "RandomState"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is effectively frozen and will only receive updates that\nare required by changes in the internals of Numpy. More substantial\nchanges, including algorithmic improvements, are reserved for\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Generator"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Extended Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Random seed used to initialize the pseudo-random number generator or\nan instantized BitGenerator.  If an integer or array, used as a seed for\nthe MT19937 BitGenerator. Values can be any integer between 0 and\n2**32 - 1 inclusive, an array (or other sequence) of such integers,\nor "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "None"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (the default).  If "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "seed"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "None"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", then the "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "MT19937"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "\nBitGenerator is initialized by reading data from "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "/dev/urandom"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "\n(or the Windows analogue) if available or seed from the clock\notherwise."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "{None, int, array_like, BitGenerator}, optional",
              "inline": [
                {
